6 million years or so, there have been
thousands of 'really wonderful new
genes' each initially spreading through
a small local population. When enough
of these 'new genes' had accumulated in
any one population (or 'sub-species')
that group would have expanded at the
expense of its neigbours (which it would
see as competitors) occasionally doing
so on a world-wide basis.

